\par }{\plain \lang1033 
\par }{\plain \lang1033 A:}{\plain \lang1033 \tab }{\plain \lang1033 You may have a very old module (created with Noise- or SoundTracker) that uses a speed setting greater or equal 32.  }{\plain \lang1033 HyperMOD}{\plain \lang1033 
 usually interprets these settings as tempos (beats per minute), but in some MODs they're meant to be ticks per division, just like values less than 32.  Since there's no way to tell which interpretation is correct, }{\plain \lang1033 HyperMOD}{\plain 
\lang1033  lets you }{\plain \ul\cf11\lang1033 Disable BPM Speeds}{\v\f2\fs16\cf5 Main_BPM}{\plain \lang1033  if necessary.  Just click the BPM symbol in th}{\plain \lang1033 e }{\plain \uldb\cf11\lang1033 Main Dialog}{\v\f2\fs16\cf5 HauptDlg}{\plain 
\lang1033 .}{\plain \lang1033 
